"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"659cc1",
"children":[
"Characteristic findings of ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"gastroesophageal reflux disease",
"children":[
"GERD"
]
},
" are heartburn and/or regurgitation."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d92e97",
"children":[
"Extraesophageal symptoms may include chest pain, cough, hoarseness, and wheezing."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1af921",
"children":[
"In a patient without alarm features (anemia, dysphagia, vomiting, weight loss), symptom relief with a ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"proton pump inhibitor",
"children":[
"PPI"
]
},
" is both diagnostic and therapeutic."
]
}
]
},
{
